definition.value: Any EC 3.4.21.* (serine endopeptidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of endopeptidase Clp (EC 3.4.21.92).
A ceramide phosphoethanolaminein which the sphingoid base and acyl group contains a total of 38 carbon atoms and 2 double bonds.
An organic cation obtained by protonation of the tertiary amino function of loperamide.
A ceramide phosphoethanolamine (38:2) in which the acyl and the sphingoid base specified is (15Z)-tetracosenoyl and tetradecasphing-4-enine respectively.
A stilbenol that is cis-resveratrol attached to a beta-D-glucopyranosiduronic acid residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage.
A beta-lactone carrying non-8-en-1-yl and 2-(2-methyl-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)ethyl substituents at positions 3 and 4 respectively.
A decanoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of carboxy group of decanoic acid with propanol.
A diglyceride in which the two acyl groups contain a total of 34 carbons and 0 double bonds.
A diacylglycerol 34:0 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are hexadecanoyl and octadecanoyl respectively.

A diacylglycerol 34:5 in which the acyl groups specified at positions 1 and 2 are (9Z)-tetradecenoyl and (5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z)-icosatetraenoyl respectively.
A 4-[2-(2-methyl-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)ethyl]-3-(non-8-en-1-yl)oxetan-2-one in which the stereocentres at positions 3 and 4 have R-configuration.
A 4-[2-(2-methyl-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)ethyl]-3-(non-8-en-1-yl)oxetan-2-one in which the stereocentres at positions 3 and 4 have S-configuration.

A member of the class of 1-benzothiophenes that is 1-benzothiophene-1,1-dioxide substituted at position 6 by a nitro group. Used as a radiosensitising agent for esophageal squamous cell carcinoma.
An aromatic ether consisting of 4-trifluoromethylphenol in which the hydrogen of the phenolic hydroxy group is replaced by a 3-(methylamino)-1-phenylpropyl group.
An N-methyl-3-phenyl-3-[4-(trifluoromethyl)phenoxy]propan-1-amine that has R configuration. [The antidepressant drug fluoxetine is a racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-fluoxetine].
An N-methyl-3-phenyl-3-[4-(trifluoromethyl)phenoxy]propan-1-amine that has S configuration. [The antidepressant drug fluoxetine is a racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-fluoxetine].
An organic cation resulting from the protonation of the amino group of (R)-fluoxetine.
A organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and one of the phosphate OH groups of carboxyphosphoric acid
An organic cation resulting from the protonation of the amino group of (S)-fluoxetine.
A hydrochloride obtained by reaction of (R)-fluoxetine with one equivalent of hydrochloric acid.
A hydrochloride obtained by reaction of (S)-fluoxetine with one equivalent of hydrochloric acid.
Any glycerolipid in which the acyl group at position 2 of the glycerol moiety is specified as palmitoyl.
The (3aS,3a'S,8aS,8a'S)-stereoisomer of chimonanthine.
Any glycerolipid in which the acyl group at position 2 of the glycerol moiety is specified as (7Z)-hexadec-7-enoyl.
beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-[alpha-L-Fucp-(1->3)]-D-Glcp6S in which the anomeric configuration of the glucose residue is beta.
Any glycerolipid in which the acyl group at position 2 of the glycerol moiety is specified as (3E)-hexadec-3-enoyl.
Any glycerolipid where the 2-acyl group is specified as palmitoleoyl.
An amino disaccharide comprising an N-acetyl-beta-muramyl residue linked (1->4) to N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine.

alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->3)-[alpha-Neup5Ac-(2->3)-beta-D-Galp-(1->4)-beta-D-GlcpNAc-(1->6)]-D-GalpNAc in which the anomeric configuration of the GalNAc residue at the reducing end is alpha.

A linear amino tetrasaccharide comprised of N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3), (1->3) and (1->6).
